casebody.data:
Charlie JACKSON, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-4191 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. November 19, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

Petitioner's "emergency writ of coram nobis" is treated as a petition for writ of mandamus and is denied without prejudice to any right Petitioner might have to raise the asserted issues on appeal of his judgment and sentence.
